<h2 class="subhead">Housing rents</h2><div style="clear:both;">Knowsley Council does not own 
accommodation within the Borough. The 
Council works with other housing 
providers such as Housing Associations 
(sometimes known as Registered Social 
Landlords, RSL&#039;s) in order to ensure 
that accommodation is available. <br />
<br />
Each Association is responsible for 
setting the level of rent that it 
charges to its tenants. However 
recently, Central Government 
introduced a new approach to setting 
rents such that Housing Associations 
and Councils would have similar levels 
of rent for similar properties. This 
is to eliminate discrepancies that 
have occurred across the country. 
The actual level of the rents is 
determined by how much each 
association needs to spend on services 
to its tenants. <br />
<br />
As part of your tenancy agreement you 
agreed to ensure that the rent would 
be paid. Each landlord will have made 
different arrangements for you to pay 
your rent. For further information 
contact your landlord or housing 
association (housing association 
contacts can be found by clicking on 
the link below).<br />
<br />
<a tabindex="316" title="Housing association contacts" href="/housing/housing_associations/association_contacts.html">Housing association contacts</a></div>
<br />
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Help paying your rent</h2>If you need help paying your rent you 
may be entitled to housing benefit. 
Click on the link below which will 
transfer you to the Council tax benefit
section.<br />
<br />
If you are falling into arrears with 
your rent do not wait for court action 
to be taken. Talk to your landlord or 
seek independent advice, do not wait 
until it&#8217;s too late.<br />
<br />
<a tabindex="318" title="Council tax benefit" href="/your_council/councils/council_tax_finance/ct_benefit.html">Council tax benefit</a></div>
<br />
